# Plan: Add /chat/:id route for deep-linking conversations (#86)

## Context

All chat happens on `/chat` with conversation state in React state. Refreshing loses the active conversation, no deep linking, browser back/forward doesn't work. This adds `/chat/$conversationId` with an optional `?message=<id>` search param for scrolling to specific messages.

## URL Scheme

| URL | Behavior |
|-----|----------|
| `/chat` | New/empty conversation |
| `/chat/:id` | Load and display conversation |
| `/chat/:id?message=<messageId>` | Load conversation, scroll to and highlight message |

## Files to Modify

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `app/src/client/router.tsx` | Add `/chat/$conversationId` route with `message` search param, update navigation |
| `app/src/client/hooks/use-chat-session.ts` | Add `useNavigate`, navigate URL on conversation lifecycle events |
| `app/src/client/routes/chat-page.tsx` | Read route params, load conversation on mount, scroll to message from search param |
| `app/src/client/stores/view-state.ts` | Remove `highlightMessageId`/`navigateToChat`/`clearHighlight` (replaced by URL) |
| `app/src/client/components/graph/EntityDetailPanel.tsx` | Update "Jump to message" to navigate to `/chat/:conversationId?message=<id>` |
| `app/src/client/components/graph/ProvenanceSection.tsx` | Update `onJumpToMessage` signature to include `conversationId` |
| `app/src/server/graph/queries.ts` | Add `conversationId` to provenance response for message sources |
| `app/src/shared/contracts.ts` | Add `conversationId` to provenance type |
| `tests/unit/graph-view-state.test.ts` | Update tests for removed `navigateToChat`/`clearHighlight` |

## Implementation

### 1. Server: Add `conversationId` to provenance (`app/src/server/graph/queries.ts`)

The provenance query selects `in` (message RecordId) from `extraction_relation`. Messages have a `conversation` field. We need to resolve it for message-type sources.

**`EntityProvenance` type** — add `conversationId?: string`:
```ts
export type EntityProvenance = {
  sourceId: string;
  sourceKind: "message" | "document_chunk" | "git_commit";
  confidence: number;
  extractedAt: string;
  conversationId?: string;  // NEW — only for sourceKind === "message"
  // ... existing fields
};
```

**Provenance query** (line ~955) — add a subquery to resolve message→conversation:
After the existing provenance query, do a second pass for message-type rows to look up their conversation. Use `FETCH` or a separate lookup:

```ts
// After collecting provenanceRows, resolve conversationIds for message sources
const messageIds = provenanceRows
  .filter((r) => r.in.table.name === "message")
  .map((r) => r.in);

if (messageIds.length > 0) {
  const [convRows] = await input.surreal
    .query<[Array<{ id: RecordId<"message", string>; conversation: RecordId<"conversation", string> }>]>(
      "SELECT id, conversation FROM message WHERE id IN $ids;",
      { ids: messageIds },
    )
    .collect<[Array<{ id: RecordId<"message", string>; conversation: RecordId<"conversation", string> }>]>();

  const convMap = new Map(convRows.map((r) => [r.id.id as string, r.conversation.id as string]));
  // Use convMap when building provenance items
}
```

Then in the mapping:
```ts
...(row.in.table.name === "message" && convMap?.get(row.in.id as string)
  ? { conversationId: convMap.get(row.in.id as string) }
  : {}),
```

**Shared contract** (`app/src/shared/contracts.ts` line ~270) — add `conversationId?: string` to provenance array type.

### 2. Router: Add parameterized chat route (`app/src/client/router.tsx`)

```ts
import { createRoute, createRouter, createRootRoute } from "@tanstack/react-router";
import { z } from "zod";  // or inline validateSearch

const chatSearchSchema = z.object({
  message: z.string().optional(),
});

const chatRoute = createRoute({
  getParentRoute: () => rootRoute,
  path: "/chat",
  component: ChatPage,
